subSections.title: Alternative forms
subSections.text:
* In mainland China, the right component is written {{l|mul|⿱[[𠆢]][[干]]}}, which is the historical form found in the {{w|Kangxi dictionary}}.
* In Taiwan, the right component is written {{l|mul|⿱[[八]][[干]]}} instead.

subSections.title: Glyph origin
subSections.text:
; Etymology 1: Found in the ''{{w|Zuo zhuan}}'' {{w2|zh|pref=《|左傳|suf=》}} (Commentary on the {{w|Spring and Autumn Annals}}) from the 4th century BC.
; Etymology 2: Found in the ''{{w|Longkan Shoujian}}'' {{w2|zh|pref=《|龍龕手鑑|suf=》}} dictionary compiled in 997 AD.
